<task id="034" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.B2 — Repair factory-dependent cluster batch 2 (config-path tests)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>2-4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, factory-dependent, p23-b, bff-api, testing</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Named config/options test files are disjoint from sibling batch 033 (auth/startup-path tests); no shared file targets</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Repair the config-path subset of the WebApplicationFactory-dependent cluster. These tests
    needed Phase 1 task 019 (P1.C) factory extension to reach the assertion phase and now exhibit
    assertion-level drift. Batch 2 covers config/options-path test files; batch 1 (task 033)
    covers auth/startup-path test files.

    Tests in scope: roughly 15-25 named config/options-path test files (e.g., `*OptionsTests.cs`,
    `*ConfigurationTests.cs`, `Infrastructure/Configuration/*.cs`). The exact file set is identified
    from Phase 0 baseline TRX failures within this category.

    For each test:
    1. Identify the broken assertion (config-bound value changed, option default changed, validation message changed)
    2. Update assertion to match current behavior — DO NOT restructure setup/teardown
    3. Apply `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` per project CLAUDE.md §6.2 taxonomy
    4. Run affected test class; verify Pass

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02 + design.md §4.1: this is repair, NOT rewrite. If ANY file's diff
    would exceed 50% line replacement, HALT and file
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-034-{FileName}.md`
    per §4.8 escalation procedure. Do NOT proceed without owner approval.

    NO production code changes (NFR-01). Per §6.2, every touched test ends in `repaired`,
    `real-bug-pending-fix`, `flaky-quarantined`, OR is archived via `*.cs.archived-2026-MM-DD`.
    `Failed` is FORBIDDEN at project close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test repair specialist with Options pattern + IConfiguration expertise.</role>

  <goal>
    ~15-25 config/options-path test files now have correct assertions. All Pass. Every touched test
    has `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="factory">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/CustomWebAppFactory.cs</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code in `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation BEFORE work proceeds</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.5">MUST NOT touch `CustomWebAppFactory.cs`</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every touched test gets a §6.2 final end-state trait</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-03">MUST NOT increase BFF DI registration count</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-15">All factory-dependent cluster tests must end in §6.2 final end-state</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The config-path subset of the factory-dependent cluster covers tests that bind options /
      validate configuration. After the factory extension (task 019) populated fake config values,
      these tests reach the assertion phase but the assertions are stale. Common patterns:
      option default changed in production, validation message text changed, additional binding
      key required. This batch is disjoint from batch 1 (auth/startup-path) enabling parallel
      execution within Wave 1 of Phase 2+3.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="019" status="not-started">CustomWebAppFactory extension verified (NFR-07 anti-parallelism)</dependency>
      <dependency task="014" status="not-started">Compile health verified after P1.A batches</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/**/*OptionsTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/**/*ConfigurationTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Infrastructure/Configuration/*.cs</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">From Phase 0 baseline TRX + Phase 1 P1.C exit notes, identify the config/options-path tests in the factory-dependent cluster. Expected ~15-25 files.</step>
    <step order="2">For each file: read the failing test; inspect current production Options class defaults and validation logic.</step>
    <step order="3">Compute pre-edit line count per file. If any planned edit exceeds 50% of file lines → HALT, file `escalations/rewrite-request-T-034-{FileName}.md`, await owner approval.</step>
    <step order="4">Group tests by failure pattern (default value changed → adjust expected; required key added → adjust setup; message text drift → adjust matcher). Apply pattern-based edits.</step>
    <step order="5">Apply `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` at class level (or per-method).</step>
    <step order="6">After each file: `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~&lt;ClassName&gt;"` verify Pass.</step>
    <step order="7">Final batch verification: cluster filter on identified files shows zero failures.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md` with file list + repair patterns observed.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify `git status` shows NO modifications under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`. Verify `CustomWebAppFactory.cs` is unchanged.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (per-file iterative + batch verification)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status (verify NFR-01)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">~15-25 config/options-path test files (repaired)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md (updated)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All identified batch-2 factory-dependent tests Pass under `dotnet test --filter`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file diff is &lt;50% line replacement (NFR-02); if exceeded, escalation file exists</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every touched test has a §6.2 final end-state trait</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows zero changes under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`CustomWebAppFactory.cs` is NOT modified</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new DI registrations added (NFR-03 preserved)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
